article.description:
Shannon Johnson had 20 points and five
assists to lead the Connecticut Sun to an 84-70 victory over the
Minnesota Lynx on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Johnson's 20 points help Sun win third straight
article.linkText: Johnson, free-throw shooting help Sun beat Lynx
article.story:
UNCASVILLE, Conn. (AP) -- Shannon Johnson had 20 points and five
assists to lead the Connecticut Sun to an 84-70 victory over the
Minnesota Lynx on Wednesday night.

Johnson was 11-for-14 from the free-throw line, and the Sun made
eight foul shots in the final 1:17 to seal Connecticut's third
straight victory.

The Sun (12-11) spoiled the homecoming of former UConn players
Tamika Williams and Svetlana Abrosimova, who now play for the Lynx
(11-10).

Four of Connecticut's starters scored in double figures. Nykesha
Sales tallied 13 of her 17 points in the first half. Taj
McWilliams-Franklin had 17 points and eight rebounds, and Katie
Douglas added 14 points.

The Sun capitalized on Minnesota's mistakes, scoring 16 points
off 23 turnovers.

Lynx guard Katie Smith was held to five points in the first
half. Smith, who scored 34 points against the Sun on July 10,
rebounded with 15 points in the second half.

Sheri Sam had 17 points and five rebounds for the Lynx. Jordan
Adams had 13 points and 10 rebounds.

Williams, playing her first game in Connecticut since graduating
from UConn last year, had four points and nine rebounds in 34
minutes. Abrosimova didn't play because of a right hamstring
strain.
